<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
(Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 41" captionStartId="F41" captionText="Figure 41. Distribution of Solanum pseudogracile Heiser." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.123.31738.figure41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/305340" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">41</figureCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pseudogracile" order="Solanales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogracile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Solanum pseudogracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the southeastern United States of America from the Atlantic coast of the Carolinas to the Gulf Coast in Florida and Alabama. Although we have seen no collections yet, we expect this species to also occur in the Bahamas.
</paragraph>
