<subSubSection pageId="83" pageNumber="84" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
Occurring on sand dunes, sandy moist banks and disturbed areas between 0-400 m elevation. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum pseudogracile" order="Solanales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudogracile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Solanum pseudogracile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is ecologically distinct from 
<taxonomicName family="Verbenaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. americanum" order="Solanales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" rank="species" species="americanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">S. americanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in growing mostly on hummocks in salt marches or on sand dunes, as an epiphyte on palm trees, on walls, and among dense hedgerows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
